<common-name datatype='string'>ycgZ-ymgA-ariR-ymgC</common-name>
<comment datatype='string'>&lt;i&gt;ycgZ-ymgA-ariR-ymgC&lt;/i&gt; constitutes an operon. YmgA and AriR activate production of the biofilm matrix substance colanic acid as well as acid resistance genes and the biofilm-associated &lt;i&gt;bdm&lt;/i&gt; gene and they downregulate adhesive curli fimbriae [&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/17222132&quot;&gt;Domka07&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/17609140&quot;&gt;Majdalani07&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/17765265&quot;&gt;Lee07a&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/19172264&quot;&gt;Attila09&lt;/a&gt;]. YcgZ appears to counteract the activities of YmgA and YmgB [&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/19240136&quot;&gt;Tschowri09&lt;/a&gt;].
&lt;p&gt;
Expression of this operon is under the control of &amp;sigma;&lt;sup&gt;38&lt;/sup&gt; (rpoS) RNA polymerase and  repressed by &lt;i&gt;ycgE&lt;/i&gt;, which is transcribed divergently on the opposite strand [&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/19240136&quot;&gt;Tschowri09&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/15716429&quot;&gt;Weber05&lt;/a&gt;].
</comment>
